            <h1>FRANCE</h1>
            <p>France, or the French Republic, is located in Western Europe. The capital city is Paris, which famous for its fashion, art, and museums.</p>     
            <p>France is one of the top tourist destination in the world for over 20 years! People from all over the world are wishing to go to France because of its culture, landmarks, fancy cuisine, romantic chateaux, and many more. In terms of fashion, Paris is known as the world fashion capital. Do you know brands Chanel, Dior, and Louis Vuitton? Yeah, they are from France!  </p>    
            <p>"France is all about world-class art and architecture, Roman temples and Renaissance chateaux, iconic landmarks known the world over, and rising stars few yet know. Stroll" (Lonely Planet, 2017).</p>
            
            <h2>Tourism</h2>
            <p>For some people who likes to travelling, France is the one-of-the-must place to go! There are some places that really interesting, and you are going to be enjoy your travel.</p>
            <p>Here are some places that you should go when you travel in France : </p>
            
            
            <h3>Paris</h3>
            <p>Paris is the most popular tourist destination in France. The places that you should go in Paris are Eiffel Tower (Tour Eiffel); Musee du Louvre, is the biggest art museum in the world, and it was the most visited museum in the 2014, you can find the great "Mona Lisa" here!;and last but not least, Notre-Dame Cathedral (Cathedrale de Notre Dame de Paris). </p>
            
            <h3>Mont Saint-Michel</h3>
            <p>In the Mont Saint-Michael, you can go to the Abbey, the museum, and the parish church. It is located in the middle of the bay, the Mont Saint-Michael. There is "Grande Rue", which you can find it after you go through the Boulevard Gate. It has its museums, shops, and also many houses that built in the 15th and the 16th centuries! So while you're traveling in Mont Saint-Michel, you can go shopping and enjoy the view! </p>
            
            <h3>Bordeaux</h3>
            <p>Bordeaux is known as its beautiful region of southwest France. It has more than 300 places and buildings that has classified as a historical monument. Because of its romantic location and environment, Bordeaux is called the "Port of the Moon". UNESCO has reported that Bordeaux is a World Heritage Site. </p>
            
            <h2>Interesting Facts:</h2>  
                <ul>
                    <li>Louis XIX, the king of France in the 1830, was only being a king for only 20 minutes.</li>
                    <li>Have you wonder could you marry a dead person? You can do it in France! </li>
                    <li>There are million of French people who are living near the Italy border speak Italian.</li>
                    <li>The world's first artificial face transplant and heart transplant took place in France.</li>
                </ul>
                
          
            <h2>FOOD</h2>
            <p>Here are some dishes that traditionally from France: </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Ratatouille</li>
                    <p>Have you watched Ratatouille movie? Yeah, it is from France! It can be served as a side dish. It is made by a stewed vegetable recipe. The ingredients are garlic, tomatoes, onions, eggplant, carrots, zucchini, bell peppers, basil, and other green herbs. So healthy and yummy!</p>
                    
                    <li>Coq au vin</li>
                    <p>Coq au vin is a dish with chicken braised with mushrooms, salt pork or bacon, wine, onions, garlic, and brandy. </p>
                    
                    <li>Cassoulet</li>
                    <p>Cassoulet it a dish that made from white beans with meats, you can choose either pork, duck, sausages, goose, or whatever else. This dish originaly come from southern France, and popular in Toulouse, Carcassonne, and Castelnaudary. </p>
                </ul>
          
